I’ve seen a lot of comments from people saying they’ve reached out to chapters and haven’t received a response. I want to tell you why...

1. After our mention on the debate stage we have been swamped with new prospects. It takes time to go through every single request. A simple example is my personal chapter where we have over a hundred members before the debates. I currently have over 750 applications in south Florida alone. We have processed only a portion of those. 

2. We have slowed down vetting because we are being extra careful on who we let in. If we let everyone in at once it has the potential to change the culture within our club. It’s quality over quantity. We have done so much with such a small group that we are not in a rush to increase our numbers. We will go through each application throughly.

So please be patient we will get to you guys. The amount of support has been overwhelming...and that we thank you for!

Proud of your patience.
